7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Continue and GitHub Copilot share a solid foundation of core features including Autocomplete, Code Generation, Debugging, Refactoring. On the other hand, GitHub Copilot uniquely offers Code Review and Test Generation and Documentation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Continue holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while GitHub Copilot scores 9/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Continue offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $0, compared to GitHub Copilot's starting price of $10/mo. Continue has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. GitHub Copilot does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
