b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Continue is best suited for developers wanting full control, teams using self hosted LLMs, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. GitHub Copilot, meanwhile, shines for developers wanting inline code suggestions, teams using GitHub workflows, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Continue describes itself as \"Open-source AI code assistant you can customize.\" GitHub Copilot, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Your AI pair programmer that suggests code in real-time.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **GitHub Copilot** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (10 vs 7). However, this does not mean Continue is a poor choice — far from it. Continue excels in its own right, particularly for developers wanting full control and teams using self hosted LLMs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value seamless github integration, go with GitHub Copilot. If fully open-source matters more to you, Continue is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
